# CameraSystem

## Purpose
Drives the orthographic camera each frame. Window-resize events update m_AspectRatio and mark the
projection dirty for ALL cameras regardless of m_ReactsToInput. For cameras with m_ReactsToInput =
true, scroll events adjust m_ZoomLevel (clamped) and WASD key presses emit a
CameraTransformRequestOneFrameComponent that pans the camera's PositionComponent (read as the current
location). Every frame it syncs the internal camera from the resolved PositionComponent and rebuilds
the projection when zoom or aspect could have changed. The camera's world position lives in its
PositionComponent (written by the transform pipeline), not on this component.

## Input Components
| Component | Access |
|---|---|
| KeyPressedEventComponent | read |
| MouseScrolledEventComponent | read |
| WindowResizeEventComponent | read |
| PositionComponent | read |
| OrthographicCameraComponent | write |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| OrthographicCameraComponent | write | Updates m_ZoomLevel, m_AspectRatio, m_CameraTranslationSpeed, and the internal view-projection matrix |
| CameraTransformRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Pan request applied by the engine TransformResolveSystem |
